'Cabuyao' (; ), or officially known as the 'City of Cabuyao' () (; PSGC:
043404000 ) is a first class city in the western portion
of Laguna, Philippines. According to the 2010 Census, it has a population of
248,436 inhabitants.

Cabuyao is formerly known as the "Richest Municipality in the Philippines" as evidenced by the large populace of migrants working in the
town's industrial estates. [http://www.wowlaguna.com/towns-and-cities/cabuyao-
laguna/ WOW Laguna - Cabuyao, Laguna] NestlÃ© Philippines, Asia Brewery,
Inc., San Miguel Corporation, Tanduay Distillers, Inc., Wyeth Philippines,
Inc., Procter & Gamble Philippines, Light Industry and Science Park of the
Philippines and Malayan Colleges Laguna have established factories or are
located in Cabuyao.

By virtue of Republic Act No. 10163, [http://www.-
senate.gov.ph/republic_acts/ra%2010163.pdf Republic Act No. 10163 - Cabuyao City
Charter] the town of Cabuyao has been converted to a Component City, [http://www.senate.gov.ph/lis/bill_res.aspx?congress=15&-
q=HBN-4259 15th Congress - House Bill No. 4259 - Senate of the
Philippines] after the ratification of a plebiscite held on August 4,
2012. [http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/243385/cabuyao-laguna-is-
newest-city Philippine Daily Inquirer - Cabuyao, Laguna, is newest
city] [http://www.comelec.gov.ph/?r=Plebiscites-
